{"id":670185,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robert_Klein","text":"Robert Klein (born February 8, 1942) is an American comedian, singer, and actor. He was born in New York City. He was nominated for a Best Actor in a Musical Tony Award for 1979's \"They're Playing Our Song\". He was known for hosting \"Saturday Night Live\" twice.\nKlein starred in many movies such as \"The Owl and the Pussycat\", \"Hooper\", \"Primary Colors\", \"Radioland Murders\", \"Ira and Abby\", \"One Fine Day\", \"Two Weeks Notice\", \"How to Lose a Guy in 10 Days\", \"The Last Unicorn\", and \"The Safety of Objects\".","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":43},{"uri":"Comedian","surface_form":"comedian","offset":52},{"uri":"Singer","surface_form":"singer","offset":62},{"uri":"Actor","surface_form":"actor","offset":74},{"uri":"New_York_City","surface_form":"New York City","offset":96},{"uri":"Tony_Award","surface_form":"Tony Award","offset":158},{"uri":"They%27re_Playing_Our_Song","surface_form":"They're Playing Our Song","offset":181},{"uri":"Saturday_Night_Live","surface_form":"Saturday Night Live","offset":234},{"uri":"The_Owl_and_the_Pussycat_(movie)","surface_form":"The Owl and the Pussycat","offset":300},{"uri":"Hooper_(movie)","surface_form":"Hooper","offset":328},{"uri":"Primary_Colors_(movie)","surface_form":"Primary Colors","offset":338},{"uri":"Radioland_Murders","surface_form":"Radioland Murders","offset":356},{"uri":"Ira_and_Abby","surface_form":"Ira and Abby","offset":377},{"uri":"One_Fine_Day_(movie)","surface_form":"One Fine Day","offset":393},{"uri":"Two_Weeks_Notice","surface_form":"Two Weeks Notice","offset":409},{"uri":"How_to_Lose_a_Guy_in_10_Days","surface_form":"How to Lose a Guy in 10 Days","offset":429},{"uri":"The_Last_Unicorn_(movie)","surface_form":"The Last Unicorn","offset":461},{"uri":"The_Safety_of_Objects","surface_form":"The Safety of Objects","offset":485}]}